content:
As you create and work with cross filters, take note of these considerations and limits.

Available in: both Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
Available in: Enhanced Folder Sharing


To add edit, or delete a cross filter in private reports:
Enhanced Folder Sharing
Create and Customize Reports

To add edit, or delete a cross filter in private and public reports:
Enhanced Folder Sharing
Report Builder OR Report Builder (Lightning Experience)

Adding cross filters can potentially slow down your report. To avoid having the report or preview time out, limit the data returned by setting filters.

Since the objects available in cross filters depend on the parent object of the report type you choose, consider the related child objects before selecting a report type.

Cross filters work in conjunction with your report type selection. Cross filters have an AND relationship with the report type you select.

In Lightning Experience, although cross filters appear on the run page, you cannot change their values on the run page.

When you filter on a Salesforce object ID, the ID must be 15 or 18 characters in length and the ID is not case-sensitive.

Each report can have up to 3 cross filters.
Each cross filter can have up to 5 subfilters.
Filter logic doesnâ€™t apply to cross filters.
title: Cross Filtering Best Practices
